cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with the problem of containing self-propagating malware using learning-based signature generation schemes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for signature generation, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The use of honeypots and intrusion detection and prevention systems falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves simulation and numerical analysis, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of learning rates, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
